action: optimize
reasoning: "Final iteration with Q3 at 4.8x gap (384ms vs 80ms DuckDB). Clear bottleneck identified: std::unordered_map in aggregation. Flat_hash_map migration (priority 1) + prefetching (priority 3) + pre-sizing (priority 4) should yield 2.3-2.9x combined speedup, bringing Q3 to ~130-165ms (within 2x of DuckDB). Q1 and Q6 are already beating/matching DuckDB. Strong positive trajectory (Q3 improved 3.1x in iteration 2). Being aggressive with final iteration - we have rollback capability."
selected_recommendations[3]: 0,2,3
focus_areas[3]: "Replace std::unordered_map with flat_hash_map in Q3 hash aggregation (2-2.5x speedup)",Add prefetching to Q3 hash table probes to hide memory latency (1.1-1.2x additional),Pre-size Q3 aggregation hash tables to eliminate rehashing (1.1-1.15x additional)
strategy_notes: "Final iteration strategy: Focus exclusively on Q3 bottleneck with complementary optimizations. Priorities 1, 3, and 4 all target Q3 and work together synergistically. Combined effect: 384ms → ~130-165ms (2.3-2.9x total improvement). This brings Q3 within 1.6-2x of DuckDB instead of 4.8x, achieving competitive performance across all queries. Not optimizing Q1 further (already 1.4x faster than DuckDB) to concentrate resources on the critical bottleneck."
notes: "Implementation sequence: (1) First apply flat_hash_map migration (priority 1) - this is the foundation. (2) Then add pre-sizing (priority 4) which depends on flat_hash_map. (3) Finally add prefetching (priority 3). All three are algorithm/CPU optimizations with low risk and no storage changes required. Expected outcome: Q3 reaches 130-165ms, closing most of the gap to DuckDB's 80ms target."